    <!-- PlaceHolder tag prevents inline radmenu.ClientID code below clashing with Utility.EnsureScriptManager(this); -->
    <script>

        $(document).ready(function () {
            giveAllMenuLinksAUniqueIdentifier();
            $(".rmLink").on("keydown", setSpacebarToOpenMenus);
        });

        function giveAllMenuLinksAUniqueIdentifier() {
            //Give all menu items a unique attribute value so that I can identify them when spacebar is clicked. Same 'menunumber' attribute is set in .aspx code on menu items.
            var index = 0;
            $(".telerik_main_menu li.rmItem a.rmLink").each(function (index) {
                $(this).attr("menunumber", index);
            });
        }

        function setSpacebarToOpenMenus(e) {
            //Open submenus on spacebar press. 
            var theKey = e.which;
            if (theKey == 32) { // 32 is keycode for spacebar. 
                var menuNumber = $(this).attr("menunumber");
                var menu = $find("ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_ctl01_radmenu");
                var menuItem = menu.findItemByAttribute("menunumber", menuNumber);
                var submenuItems = menuItem.get_items();
                if (submenuItems.get_count() > 0) {
                    if (menuItem.get_isOpen() == false) {
                        menuItem.open();
                        e.preventDefault();
                    };
                };
            };
        };

        function ClickItem(menu, args) {
            //Event set in OnClientItemClicking="ClickItem";
            //When user clicks (presses Enter key) a menu item, if submenu is not open, then open it; otherwise navigate to the item's link. 
            var item = args.get_item();
            var submenuItems = item.get_items();
            if (submenuItems.get_count() > 0) {
                //If submenu is closed, then open it; otherwise click the menu item link. 
                if (item.get_isOpen() == false) {
                    args.set_cancel(true); //Cancel the default click action so that it doesn't trigger the menu item's navigation link.
                    item.open();
                }
                else {
                    if (typeof item.redirectToLink == 'undefined') {
                        item.redirectToLink = true;
                        item.click();
                    } else {
                        delete item.redirectToLink;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

    </script>

<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><a name="general_travel_advice"></a></span></p>
<h2><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(20, 168, 125);"><strong>General Travel Advice</strong></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Contact your airline prior to all travel, to inquire about transit  visas or any other requirements for travel both domestically and  internationally. A transit visa may be required, even for layovers in  countries other than your final destination. Please review <a href="http://www.tsa.gov/traveler-information">TSA requirements</a> prior to travel.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><a name="visa"></a></span></p>
<h3></h3>
<h2><strong><span style="font-size: 32px;">Visa</span> </strong></h2>
<strong> </strong>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">A visa is affixed in your passport by the U.S. Consulate or Embassy  abroad and allows you to travel to the U.S. It only needs to be valid  for your <em>entry</em> into the U.S., and does not have to remain valid  throughout your stay in the U.S., provided that you maintain your  immigration status. If you travel outside of the U.S. and need to  re-enter, you must have a valid/unexpired visa to return. There are  exceptions to this rule for travel to Canada, Mexico, and the adjacent  islands.*<em><br>
*See &ldquo;Automatic Visa Revalidation&rdquo; below.</em></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><a name="form_i-94"></a></span></p>
<h2><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(20, 168, 125);"><strong> Form I-94 </strong><strong> </strong></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">An I-94 is an arrival and departure record that you receive at  the Port of Entry (such as the airport) when entering the U.S. Individuals arriving to the U.S. after 04/26/2013 may <a href="https://i94.cbp.dhs.gov/I94/#/home">print the I-94 online</a>. Prior to 04/26/2013 the I-94 was a paper form filled out at the Port of Entry or on the airplane. Your I-94 must remain valid at  all times. When departing the U.S., you will turn in your I-94 paper card (if applicable),  unless you are taking advantage of AVR.* If you forget to return your  I-94 when exiting the U.S. permanently, you should&nbsp; <a href="https://help.cbp.gov/cgi-bin/customs.cfg/php/enduser/std_adp.php?p_faqid=752&amp;p_created=1077641280&amp;p_sid=9VyH5fGh&amp;p_lva=&amp;p_sp=cF9zcmNoPTEmcF9zb3J0X2J5PSZwX2dyaWRzb3J0PSZwX3Jvd19jbnQ9NDcmcF9wcm9kcz0yMywzMiZwX2NhdHM9MCZwX3B2PTIuMzImcF9jdj0mcF9zZWFyY2hfdHlwZT1">follow instructions</a> to make an effort to send it back to Department of Homeland Security (DHS/immigration).&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><a name="obtain_renew"></a></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong> </strong></span></p>
<h2><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(20, 168, 125);"><strong> How Do I Obtain or Renew A Visa?</strong></span></h2>
<ul>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">When applying for a new visa, please find out:
    </span>
    <ul>
        <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">whether an appointment is required, and<a href="https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/us-visas.html"> how long</a> it may take to process your request.</span></li>
        <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">what documents, forms, photos and fees are required</span></li>
        <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">if they allow visa applications from third country nationals (&ldquo;TCNs&rdquo;)</span></li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Be prepared to show evidence of your financial resources.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Bring appropriate immigration documents: Form I-20, DS-2019, or I-797 <em>(See &ldquo;Quick Reference</em><em> Table&rdquo; below)</em></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">If an initial F-1 or J-1, pay the <a href="http://www.ice.gov/sevis/i901/">SEVIS fee</a>.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Schedule a flight that allows sufficient time for you to obtain a  visa.&nbsp; Additional security checks are possible for certain individuals,  which may result in delays of 30+ business days.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Make sure your passport is valid for 6 months from date of visa application.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Check with local <a href="http://www.usembassy.gov/">U.S. Embassy or Consulate</a> for possible additional documentation needed.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">If you need a new visa and you travel outside the U.S., be aware  that you are never guaranteed that a new visa will be issued, especially  if you apply at a U.S. embassy or consulate in a country other than  your home country.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">If you travel to a country other than your home country, you may  need a visa to enter that country.&nbsp; Check that country&rsquo;s immigration  website for more information.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">You may need a transit visa if arriving in a third country en route to another country.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">If you have changed status within the U.S. and now want to travel  outside of the U.S., you will need to obtain a new entry visa to match  your current status to return to the U.S.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><a href="https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/us-visas/tourism-visit/citizens-of-canada-and-bermuda.html">Canadian citizens: no visa required except for statuses A, G, E, K, and V</a> A passport is required for air travel, <a href="http://www.getyouhome.gov/html/eng_map.html">but not necessarily by land or sea</a>.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong> </strong></span></p>

<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><a name="avr"></a></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong> </strong></span></p>
<h3></h3>
<h2><strong><span style="font-size: 32px; color: rgb(20, 168, 125);">Automatic Visa Revalidation (AVR)</span></strong></h2>
<strong> </strong>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> </span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong>Definition:</strong> <em>Your expired U.S. entry visa is considered to be </em><em>automatically  extended to the date of reentry provided that the visa has not been  canceled, and that you have not applied for a new visa. To take  advantage of AVR your travel must be to contiguous territories and for  less than 30 days.&nbsp; Rules governing AVR are found in the United State&rsquo;s <a href="http://edocket.access.gpo.gov/cfr_2002/aprqtr/pdf/22cfr41.112.pdf">Code of Federal Regulation</a>.<br>
</em></span></p>
<ul>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Contiguous countries are: Canada, Mexico, and the adjacent islands:  Saint Pierre, Miquelon, the Dominican Republic, Haiti, Bermuda, the  Bahamas, Barbados, Jamaica, the Windward and Lee Islands, Trinidad,  Martinique, the other British, French and Netherlands territories or  possessions in or bordering on the Caribbean Sea</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Does not apply to individuals from Cuba, Syria, Sudan&nbsp;or Iran</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong>Do not</strong> surrender your paper I-94 card when departing U.S.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">If the flight attendant or officer asks for a paper I-94 politely inform them that you are taking advantage of the AVR provision</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Only for travel less than 30 days</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong>Not</strong> valid for people who travel from a contiguous  territory, such as Canada, to a non-contiguous country, such as Germany,  and return to the U.S. via a contiguous territory</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong>H-1B workers</strong> are only allowed to take advantage of  AVR for travel to Canada and Mexico ONLY Mexican nationals traveling to  Mexico, must have a valid U.S. visa to reenter the U.S.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">If you have changed your status while in the U.S. and hold a visa  for the previous status, you may still take advantage of AVR, as long as  you bring the supporting documents for your new status (see the <em>&ldquo;Quick Reference Table&rdquo;</em> above).&nbsp; For example, you changed your status from F-1 to H-1B, but still only have an expired F-1 visa; you may still use AVR.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><a name="enter_the_us"></a></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong> </strong></span></p>
<h2><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(20, 168, 125);"><strong>Entering the U.S. &ndash; General Information</strong></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong> </strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">For the most accurate information regarding entry procedures to the U.S., please see the <a href="http://www.cbp.gov/travel/international-visitors">U.S. Customs and Border Patrol website</a>.  At this site you will find information regarding customs regulations,  AVR, Form I-94, the Visa Waiver Program and other useful updates to help  you with your travels to the U.S.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><a name="obtain_in_canada"></a></span></p>
<h3></h3>
<h2><strong><span style="font-size: 32px; color: rgb(20, 168, 125);">Obtaining or Renewing Your Visa in Canada or Mexico</span></strong></h2>
<strong> </strong>
<ul>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">First, check to see if you need a visitor visa to <em>enter</em> Canada or Mexico (see <em>&ldquo;Visas for Canada/Mexico&rdquo;</em>  below). Canada and Mexico have their own immigration systems and have  different bi-lateral agreements with each country regarding visas.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Research the procedure for making a visa appointment in your desired consulate.
    </span>
    <ul>
        <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong>Canada </strong>
        </span>
        <ul>
            <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><a href="https://ais.usvisa-info.com/en-ca/niv"><strong>Visa Appointment Information</strong></a></span></li>
            <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong>Consulates:</strong> Calgary, Halifax, Montreal, Ottawa, Quebec City, Toronto, Vancouver</span></li>
        </ul>
        </li>
        <li><span style="color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong>Mexico</strong>
        </span>
        <ul>
            <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><a href="https://ais.usvisa-info.com/en-mx/niv"><strong>Visa Appointment Information</strong></a><strong> </strong></span></li>
            <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong>Consulates:</strong> Ciudad Juarez, Guadalajara, Hermosillo, Matamoros, Merida, Mexico City, Monterrey, Nogales, Nuevo Laredo and Tijuana</span></li>
        </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Check current <a href="https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/us-visas.html">visa processing wait times with the Department of State.</a></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">Wait at least 5 days after booking the appointment before purchasing  your ticket for travel.&nbsp; The&nbsp; Consulate may make cancellations during  that time.</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">If you miss your appointment, you may be charged a fee, unless  canceled in advance. If you miss your appointment and do not cancel in  time, you will not be allowed to make another one until 3 months after  the date of your original appointment.</span></li>
    <li><span style="color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong>Automatic visa revalidation will no longer be available if  you apply for a new U.S. entry visa in Canada, Mexico or the adjacent  islands.</strong>
    </span>
    <ul>
        <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">The visa must be approved before you can reenter the U.S. If the  visa is denied, or subject to a security check, you must return to your  home country to obtain a new visa and may not use AVR.</span></li>
        <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">If the visa application requires a security check, you cannot  reenter the U.S. under automatic visa revalidation while the application  is pending.</span></li>
    </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><a name="visa_for_canada"></a></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong> </strong></span></p>

<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);"><strong> </strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 99, 99);">You may require a visa to <em>enter</em> Canada/Mexico. For more information consult the following sources:</span></p>
